# receipt-throttle-watch tunables for cluster uds-tenant (see box-scripts/README.md).
# All optional — unset values fall back to the script defaults. This sample is
# installed to /etc/receipt-throttle-watch/uds-tenant.env and read by the
# receipt-throttle-watch@uds-tenant.service unit.
#
# Explicit kubeconfig path for a cluster that is NOT a local-k3d-by-name cluster
# (e.g. an external/multi-node tenant). Leave unset for a local k3d cluster.
#KUBECONFIG_FILE=
# receipts-server namespace and the pod selector / container to exec /metrics in.
#RNS=szl-receipts
#RX_SELECTOR=app.kubernetes.io/name=szl-receipts-server
#RX_CONTAINER=receipts-server
# Port the server serves /metrics on inside the pod.
#METRICS_PORT=8080
# On-disk receipt store path inside the pod (used only to name the subject).
#RECEIPT_STORE=/data/receipts
# pepr controller coords (secondary subject hint) + log scan window.
#PNS=pepr-system
#PDEPLOY=pepr-szl
#SINCE=10m
# Sustained shed-rate (requests/min) at/above which to ALERT.
#THROTTLE_PER_MIN=10
# Minimum seconds between samples before a rate is computed.
#MIN_INTERVAL_SECS=60
